The paper discusses a new model for peer-to-peer networking that takes into account network bottlenecks beyond access, which is a key feature of computer networks and falls under the category of computer networking (cs.NI). The paper also analyzes the spatial interactions of peers, which is a topic in spatial information science (cs.SI). The use of mathematical analysis and dimensional analysis suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of file sharing systems, which could fall under the category of performance evaluation and optimization (cs.PF).
